<FlowDocument xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
              xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
              Foreground="#E0E0E0"
              Background="#1E1F22"
              FontFamily="Segoe UI"
              FontSize="14"
              PagePadding="32,24,32,24">

    <Paragraph FontSize="28" FontWeight="Bold" Foreground="#FFD700" Margin="0,0,0,4">
        Overview / Getting Started
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Foreground="#A0A0A0" FontSize="13" Margin="0,0,0,16">
        An overview of the Mission Editor interface, menus, quick actions, mission viewport, event point panels, map loading, light loading, and zone controls.
    </Paragraph>

    <BlockUIContainer>
        <Border Height="1" Background="#444" Margin="0,0,0,12"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF" Margin="0,4,0,4">
        What the Mission Editor Does
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        The Mission Editor is used to create and edit playable Urban Chaos mission files. A mission
        file defines the mission name, map, light file, mission properties, event points, objectives,
        sub-objectives, bonuses, messages, NPCs, items, traps, camera sequences, mission endings,
        and many other mission-specific behaviours.
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="0,6,0,0">
        Mission editing is driven almost entirely by <Bold>Event Points</Bold>. Every important
        mission action is represented by one or more event points. These event points can create the
        player, spawn enemies, place items, trigger messages, run cutscenes, start timers, award
        bonuses, end the mission, and link mission logic together.
    </Paragraph>

    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,6,0,8">
        <Image Source="pack://application:,,,/UrbanChaosMissionEditor;component/Help/Images/mission_overview_full_window.png"
               MaxWidth="720" Stretch="Uniform"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,8,0,8">
        <Border Background="#2A2F3A" BorderBrush="#4A5A7A" BorderThickness="1"
                CornerRadius="4" Padding="12">
            <TextBlock TextWrapping="Wrap" Foreground="#AFC8FF">
                <Run FontWeight="Bold">Core concept:</Run>
                <Run>
                    A mission is not just a map with objects on it. It is a network of Event Points.
                    The map provides the space; the Event Points provide the mission logic.
                </Run>
            </TextBlock>
        </Border>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <BlockUIContainer>
        <Border Height="1" Background="#444" Margin="0,14,0,12"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF" Margin="0,0,0,4">
        Main Interface Layout
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        The Mission Editor follows the same general style as the other Urban Chaos editors. The
        centre of the window is the map viewport, with mission information and event point controls
        arranged around it.
    </Paragraph>

    <List MarkerStyle="Disc" Margin="16,2,0,0">
        <ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>Status bar</Bold> — shown along the bottom of the window. It displays event messages such as adding, removing, editing, copying, or pasting event points.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>Zoom controls</Bold> — located at the bottom-left of the map area. These include zoom controls and a reset zoom button.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>Menu bar</Bold> — includes File, Edit, Zones, View, and Help menus.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>Quick action toolbar</Bold> — provides fast buttons for opening missions, loading maps, loading lights, editing linked files, and opening the 3D viewport.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>Mission Info panel</Bold> — appears when a mission is active. It shows mission metadata and loaded file references.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>Event Points panel</Bold> — shown on the right. It contains the list of event points in the loaded mission.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>Event Point Details panel</Bold> — shows the raw details for the currently selected event point.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>Viewport</Bold> — displays the map, event points, mission layers, map layers, light layers, and zone overlays.</Paragraph></ListItem>
    </List>

    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,6,0,8">
        <Image Source="pack://application:,,,/UrbanChaosMissionEditor;component/Help/Images/mission_overview_layout_annotated.png"
               MaxWidth="720" Stretch="Uniform"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF" Margin="0,12,0,4">
        Status Bar and Zoom Controls
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        The status bar is used for editor feedback. For example, it can show when an event point has
        been added, removed, selected, edited, copied, or pasted.
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="0,6,0,0">
        The zoom controls on the bottom-left of the viewport allow you to zoom in, zoom out, and
        reset the zoom level. These are useful when placing event points precisely on a large map.
    </Paragraph>

    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,6,0,8">
        <Image Source="pack://application:,,,/UrbanChaosMissionEditor;component/Help/Images/mission_overview_status_zoom.png"
               MaxWidth="720" Stretch="Uniform"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <BlockUIContainer>
        <Border Height="1" Background="#444" Margin="0,14,0,12"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF" Margin="0,0,0,4">
        File Menu
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        The File menu contains commands for creating, opening, saving, closing, and configuring
        mission files and related map/light resources.
    </Paragraph>

    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,6,0,8">
        <Image Source="pack://application:,,,/UrbanChaosMissionEditor;component/Help/Images/mission_overview_file_menu.png"
               MaxWidth="720" Stretch="Uniform"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#E8B84B" Margin="8,8,0,1">New</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="24,0,0,0">Starts a new <Run FontFamily="Consolas" Foreground="#E8B84B">.UCM</Run> mission file.</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#E8B84B" Margin="8,8,0,1">Open</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="24,0,0,0">Opens an existing <Run FontFamily="Consolas" Foreground="#E8B84B">.UCM</Run> mission file.</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#E8B84B" Margin="8,8,0,1">Save</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="24,0,0,0">Saves the current mission file.</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#E8B84B" Margin="8,8,0,1">Save As</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="24,0,0,0">Saves the current mission file as a new file.</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#E8B84B" Margin="8,8,0,1">Close</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="24,0,0,0">Closes the application.</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#E8B84B" Margin="8,8,0,1">Open Map...</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="24,0,0,0">Loads an arbitrary map file into the viewport for display. This does not have to be the map currently referenced by the mission file.</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#E8B84B" Margin="8,8,0,1">Open Lights...</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="24,0,0,0">Loads an arbitrary light file into the viewport for display. This does not have to be the light file currently referenced by the mission file.</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#E8B84B" Margin="8,8,0,1">Mission Properties</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="24,0,0,0">Opens mission properties such as crime rate, boredom rate, civilian count, map file, light file, and other mission-level settings.</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#E8B84B" Margin="8,8,0,1">Exit</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="24,0,0,0">Exits the application.</Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF" Margin="0,12,0,4">
        Edit Menu
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        The Edit menu contains commands for creating, editing, copying, pasting, and navigating
        event points.
    </Paragraph>

    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,6,0,8">
        <Image Source="pack://application:,,,/UrbanChaosMissionEditor;component/Help/Images/mission_overview_edit_menu.png"
               MaxWidth="720" Stretch="Uniform"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <List MarkerStyle="Disc" Margin="16,2,0,0">
        <ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>Add Event Point</Bold> — adds a new event point to the mission.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>Edit Event Point</Bold> — opens the selected event point for editing.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>Copy / Paste EventPoint</Bold> — copies the selected event point and pastes it at the current cursor position.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>Center on Selected</Bold> — centers the viewport on the selected event point if it is not currently visible.</Paragraph></ListItem>
    </List>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF" Margin="0,12,0,4">
        Zones Menu
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        Zones are mission overlays painted onto map cells. They can mark areas with special mission
        behaviour, such as no-go cells, colour zones, no-wander cells, and other zone types explained
        in later sections.
    </Paragraph>

    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,6,0,8">
        <Image Source="pack://application:,,,/UrbanChaosMissionEditor;component/Help/Images/mission_overview_zones_menu.png"
               MaxWidth="720" Stretch="Uniform"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <List MarkerStyle="Disc" Margin="16,2,0,0">
        <ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>Paint Zone Mode</Bold> — enables zone painting mode so selected zone types can be added to map cells.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>Erase Zone Mode</Bold> — enables zone erasing mode so zoning can be removed from map cells.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>Zone Type</Bold> — sets the current zone type used by paint or erase mode.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>Clear All Zones</Bold> — clears all zone tiles from the mission. Use this carefully, as it removes all painted zone information.</Paragraph></ListItem>
    </List>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF" Margin="0,12,0,4">
        View Menu
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        The View menu controls the 3D viewport, zoom level, and visible layer groups.
    </Paragraph>

    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,6,0,8">
        <Image Source="pack://application:,,,/UrbanChaosMissionEditor;component/Help/Images/mission_overview_view_menu.png"
               MaxWidth="720" Stretch="Uniform"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <List MarkerStyle="Disc" Margin="16,2,0,0">
        <ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>Open 3D Viewport</Bold> — opens the map in 3D with map layers, lights, prims, buildings, textures, and mission elements.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>Zoom In / Zoom Out</Bold> — changes the viewport zoom level.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>Reset Zoom</Bold> — returns the viewport to the standard zoom level.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>Mission Layers</Bold> — toggles mission-specific layers on and off.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>Map Layers</Bold> — toggles map-related layers such as textures, buildings, and objects.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>Light Layers</Bold> — toggles light-related layers such as lights and ranges.</Paragraph></ListItem>
    </List>

    <BlockUIContainer>
        <Border Height="1" Background="#444" Margin="0,14,0,12"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF" Margin="0,0,0,4">
        Quick Action Toolbar
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        The quick action toolbar gives fast access to the most common Mission Editor workflows.
    </Paragraph>

    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,6,0,8">
        <Image Source="pack://application:,,,/UrbanChaosMissionEditor;component/Help/Images/mission_overview_quick_actions.png"
               MaxWidth="720" Stretch="Uniform"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#E8B84B" Margin="8,8,0,1">Open</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="24,0,0,0">Quickly opens a <Run FontFamily="Consolas" Foreground="#E8B84B">.UCM</Run> mission file.</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#E8B84B" Margin="8,8,0,1">Map</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="24,0,0,0">Selects a custom map for display if no map is loaded, or replaces the map currently shown in the viewport.</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#E8B84B" Margin="8,8,0,1">Edit Map</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="24,0,0,0">Passes the currently loaded map to the Map Editor. A file synchronisation service updates changes made in the Map Editor in real time.</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#E8B84B" Margin="8,8,0,1">Lights</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="24,0,0,0">Selects a custom light file if no light file is loaded, or replaces the light file currently shown in the viewport.</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#E8B84B" Margin="8,8,0,1">Edit Lights</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="24,0,0,0">Passes the currently loaded light file to the Light Editor. The same file synchronisation service updates changes in real time.</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#E8B84B" Margin="8,8,0,1">3D</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="24,0,0,0">Opens the current mission/map view in the 3D viewport.</Paragraph>

    <BlockUIContainer>
        <Border Height="1" Background="#444" Margin="0,14,0,12"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF" Margin="0,0,0,4">
        Event Point Panels
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        The right side of the editor contains the Event Points list and Event Point Details panel.
        The Event Points list contains every event point in the loaded mission. Selecting an event
        point updates the details panel and highlights the point in the viewport.
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="0,6,0,0">
        The Event Point Details panel is a raw-style view of the selected event point. It is useful
        for checking identifiers, type data, position, grouping, and other low-level values.
    </Paragraph>

    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,6,0,8">
        <Image Source="pack://application:,,,/UrbanChaosMissionEditor;component/Help/Images/mission_overview_event_panels.png"
               MaxWidth="720" Stretch="Uniform"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

</FlowDocument>
